A second text for our assessment of religion is [John] Philip, Edward Edwards’// “Africa. Character of Africaner//”. The interactions between Livingstone and Africaner in the text bring to the fore various religious dimensions that are worth our analysis.


:: Asonzeh Ukah(2013) {"position":"250,650","size":"100,100"}
 //Power, politics and Pentecostal in Yorubaland//, analyses the growth of Pentecostalism in Yorubaland and its impact on Yoruba culture and society.


:: Colonization {"position":"400,300","size":"100,100"}

The analysis of colonization shall focus on Solomon Plaatje’s //Mhudi// and Weah Bye’s “The Liberian War. To the Editor of the Times”. To begin, the setting of the Mhudi unveils the effect of Europeans coming to the African coast. The people most affected by the invasion of the colonizers are the BaRolong people, who face various forms of oppression and exploitation at the hands of the Europeans. These acts of the Europeans include their attempt to take over the land of the Barolong people, distract their socio-cultural lives and impose on the Barolong people the European culture and language. We must note that the Barolong people attempt fighting to resist these impositions in order to maintain their identity.  The following are critical texts that would be used for this analysis:
[[Weah Bye]]

[[Frantz Fanon (2004)]]

[[Walter Rodney(1982)]]

[[Terence Ranger(1983)]]


